parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The deterioration of the engine harness wiring can cause forced limp mode, malfunctioning of various systems, and even complete failure of the vehicle, leading to safety risks, accidents, and financial burdens on owners.
symptoms: Engine harness wiring cracks
exposed wires
forced limp mode
malfunctioning of various systems
unreliable startup
shorts
smoke
and complete failure of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine wire harness can cause the engine to stall or shut down without warning, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine suddenly stops or stalls without warning
the "Check Engine" light illuminates on the dashboard
the vehicle may experience a loss of power or difficulty restarting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and failure can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and sudden stops, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears
the transmission makes unusual noises or vibrations
the vehicle hesitates or stalls when accelerating
the transmission warning light is illuminated on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and failure can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and sudden stops, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off while driving
the engine makes unusual noises or vibrations
the vehicle hesitates or stalls when accelerating
the check engine light is illuminated on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake failure and spongy pedal can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels further than usual
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the brake warning light is illuminated on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear defroster can reduce visibility through the rear window, increasing the risk of accidents, especially during inclement weather conditions.
symptoms: The rear defroster does not turn on
the rear defroster is not heating
the rear window remains fogged or iced
reduced visibility through the rear window.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty oil pressure gauge can lead to engine damage or failure due to low oil pressure, which can cause premature wear, overheating, and potentially result in costly repairs or even engine replacement.
symptoms: The oil pressure gauge does not move or remains stuck on zero
the oil pressure gauge fluctuates erratically
the oil pressure gauge reads incorrectly
the oil pressure warning light illuminates.
